e Groag, Fanny HarlfingerZakucka, Yella Hertzka, Else Hofmann, Hilda Jesser, Maria Likarz, Madame d'Ora, Pauline Metternich-Sándor, Bertha Pappenheim, Marie ReidemeisterNeurath, Lisl Weil, Vally Wieselthier and Helene Wolf Introduction and two chapters in English  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4a20. Jahrhundert. 4aBerta Zuckerkandl. 4aBertha Pappenheim. 4aDesign. 4aElse Hofmann. 4aEmilie Flöge. 4aFanny Harlfinger-Zakucka. 4aHelene Wolf. 4aHilda Jesser. 4aJacqueline Groag. 4aJudenverfolgung. 4aKunst. 4aKünstlerinnen. 4aLisl Weil. 4aMAK Wien. 4aMadame d'Ora. 4aMaria Likarz. 4aMarie Reidemeister-Neurath. 4aMathilde Flögl. 4aNationalsozialismus. 4aPauline Metternich-Sándor. 4aVally Wieselthier. 4aWiener Moderne. 7aART / History / Modern (late 19th Century to 1945).2bisacsh  a20th century.  aBerta Zuckerkandl.  aBertha Pappenheim.  aElse Hofmann.  aEmilie Flöge.  aFanny Harlfinger-Zakucka.  aHelene Wolf.  aHilda Jesser.  aJacqueline Groag.  aLisl Weil.  aMAK Vienna.  aMadame d'Ora.  aMaria Likarz.  aMarie Reidemeister-Neurath.  aMathilde Flögl.  aPauline Metternich-Sándor.  aVally Wieselthier.  aViennese Modernism.  aart.  adesign.  apersecution of Jews.  awomen artists.1 aBrandow-Faller, Megan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBurke, Christopher, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHölters, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKrautgartner, Lena, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKrippner, Ulrike, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relator